# Stranger agent safety live wire (SASCIP wired)

**Law:** `docs/STRANGER_AGENT_SAFETY_CONTROL_PIPELINE_LOCKED_v1.md`  
**Gate:** `bash scripts/validate-stranger-agent-safety-live-wire-v1.sh`

## Pipeline (every session — automatic)

```text
ADMIT → PROBE → PANIC → WATCH → SERVE
```

| Stage | What | Receipt |
|-------|------|---------|
| ADMIT | SASCIP fingerprint + trust tier | `~/.sina/stranger-agent-admission-receipt-v1.json` |
| PROBE | Sentinel cross-lane checks (lane ok · SSOT blocked · brain blocked) | live wire `chains.sentinel_probes` |
| PANIC | Mac emergency + agent-cancel flags | live wire `panic` |
| WATCH | Stranger watch pulse (when stale) | `~/.sina/stranger-agent-watch-receipt-v1.json` |
| SERVE | `sascip_safety_line` on live surfaces | `~/.sina/stranger-agent-safety-live-wire-v1.json` |

Session gate runs this via `stranger_agent_safety_live_wire` step.

## Before ANY disk edit (mandatory)

```bash
python3 scripts/pre_write_guard_v1.py check --agent cursor --path "<target>" --json
```

If `ok: false` → **STOP** — no write. Strangers need founder `EDIT ALLOWED: <path>` + `ACTION:` or bounded `WORK:`.

## Hub API (read-only posture)

- `GET /api/stranger-agent-safety-v1` — live wire receipt  
- `GET /api/pre-write-guard-v1?path=<abs-or-rel>&agent=cursor` — would this write be allowed?

## Quote in replies

`sascip_safety_line` from `~/.sina/agent-live-surfaces-v1.json` (paired with `factory_now_line`).
